issue.title: build error : This is caused by library dependencies that have been compiled using Java 8 or above.

repository.name: leakcanary
repository.description: A memory leak detection library for Android.

issue.body:
Detail:

Error:Error converting bytecode to dex:
Cause: Dex cannot parse version 52 byte code.
This is caused by library dependencies that have been compiled using Java 8 or above.
If you are using the 'java' gradle plugin in a library submodule add 
targetCompatibility = '1.7'
sourceCompatibility = '1.7'
to that submodule's build.gradle file.

issue.title: LeakCanary 1.5.3: Error converting bytecode to dex with RetroLambda

repository.name: leakcanary
repository.description: A memory leak detection library for Android.

issue.body:
This is similar to issue #861 

I'm using 
```
debugCompile 'com.squareup.leakcanary:leakcanary-android:1.5.3'
releaseCompile 'com.squareup.leakcanary:leakcanary-android-no-op:1.5.3'
...
compileOptions {
    sourceCompatibility JavaVersion.VERSION_1_8
    targetCompatibility JavaVersion.VERSION_1_8
}

```
with Retrolambda but gradle is throwing an exception:

```
Error:Error converting bytecode to dex:
Cause: Dex cannot parse version 52 byte code.
This is caused by library dependencies that have been compiled using Java 8 or above.
If you are using the 'java' gradle plugin in a library submodule add 
targetCompatibility = '1.7'
sourceCompatibility = '1.7'
to that submodule's build.gradle file.
```

Version 1.5.1 compiles just fine. 
it seems like the library requires java 7 and fails to build using java8 with retrolambda. 

I'm using Android gradle plugin 2.3.3

is there anything I can do? do I need to switch to AGP 3.0 to upgrade?
